article.headline: Tulane 77, Southern Miss. 72
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Andrew Garcia came off the bench to score a career-high 23 points and David Gomez had 20 points and 10 rebounds as Tulane beat Southern Mississippi 77-72 Saturday. Tulane (14-12, 7-7 Conference USA) swept the season series with the Golden Eagles (17-10, 7-7 C-USA) for the first since the 2001-02 season. Garcia hit all three of his field goal attempts and scored 12 points in the first half, which ended with the Green Wave 42-35. Although Tulane never trailed and led by as many as 11 points in the second period, Southern Miss made a late 11-3 spurt including seven points from freshman Jeremy Wise, who led all scorers with 25 points and hit a jump shot that pulled the Golden Eagles to within three points, 70-67, with 1:23 left. Courtney Beasley had 12 points and Sai'Quon Stone a game-best 12 rebounds for the Golden Eagles. Wise hit a 3-point shot with less than a minute left to bring Southern Miss within 3 points again, but Garcia grabbed a missed jump shot in a group of Southern Miss players, was immediately fouled and hit both free throw attempts. The teams traded free throws in the final seconds. Garcia hit 9-of-11 field goal attempts, his only 3-point attempt, and all four of his free throws.
